OK So last Night went Extremely well I thought, It was hell trying to get down there, I was running around trying to get everything together that I had to do. Then I took off for South Philly to Pick up Coral, then made our way to the club. Coral was thinking she would get Issues with the doorman again , but when we walked in he was busy doing something Else so we just rolled thru the door. Note to Self, this is a bad thing, anyone could have come in the same way. We Only had the Upstairs Till Midnight, some punk band playing downstairs, But its Philly and its a Late crowd Anyway, So things worked out. People were having a really good time, I was actually talking to new people and old faces all night . Took a damn shitload of pictures. Had a really great time. Helped tear down the lights for the night, and took Coral home. Special thanx goes out to Cherie and Friends for coming all the way down to be apart of our night. And to Meghan who although really didn't like the place Did come out last night . We really appreciate the support

Your Brain Usage Profile

Auditory : 52%
Visual : 47%
Left : 40%
Right : 60%

 Andy, you are moderately right-hemisphere dominant and have even preferences between auditory and visual processing, traits that might make people perceive you as "slightly off balance."

You are most likely to be slightly disorganized, a "dreamer" and a person who focuses more on the end result than the immediate task at hand. You are creative and spontaneous if somewhat lacking in direction and focus. You are a learner who is generally patient and a person for whom time is an ally, not an enemy.

You are more passionate than most people with regard to life and learning and recognize your own intuitive abilities. You have sufficient goal-direction to satisfy yourself and guarantee success without being or feeling driven. You are willing to be reflective about yourself and others without getting lost in rumination.

The balance of your sensory modes allows for both learning and expressive capabilities achieved by few. You are active and "seeing" while retaining an equally strong propensity for being reflective which slows you down a little but allows for a more comprehensive perception and analysis of situations and problems. You do not spend excessive time analyzing since you mostly trust your perceptions.

In all likelihood, you have a tendency to overcommit and cannot under- stand why others get upset since you operate on a different "time table" than they do. Your organizational abilities are frequently overwhelmed by the stimulation seeking and active nature of your mind as well as by the tendency to create new categories and gloss over details, making categorization and classification almost impossible at times.

To the extent that your career path allows for creativity and abstraction as well as a bit of disorganization, you should find yourself equipped to handle any learning that is required. Your own personal adjustment to your style should come naturally although you are likely to feel frus- trated by your own limited discipline and often wonder "Why?"

Well I attended Vesago Last night. Dj Schmitty and myself papered the hell out of that place, and I worked my ass off talking to people and giving them fliers. I hope it wasn't all for not and we get a good crowd out. I am also working a couple side ideas right now to try and bring some industrial back to Jersey. And thank god I have Rad to confer with or I would still be completely lost with a lot of it. He is a HUGE help. And thanx to Clint who also gave me some pointers and ideas to run with. Anyway back to last night, I went to Delaware to pick up Laura and brought her with me to Vesago. She got pretty trashed but still had a decent time, then she convinced me to go to south st and pick up Pizza, which I have to say she was right it was kick ass. Then when we got back to her house I was so beat she was nice enough to let me crash there.  I put her to bed :) and no nothing perverted I just wouldn't let her sleep on the floor where she started to crash at in the first place. then in the morning I made my way home. With a shit load of ideas running thru my head.  My brain never stops , and once I put a focus to it, its just crazy. but I will see where some of this goes, all you jersey people cross your fingers I am trying hard to bring the scene back in Jersey. You guys just have to come out and support the scene and I know you will.
